Good morning Jennifer,

Thank you for the information. I understand the concern and the impact this had on patient care.

To clarify, the AE Title was not arbitrarily “turned off.” On 03/11/2026, an inbound connection associated with the new CT scanner was identified with an unrecognized/unknown AE Title. In accordance with standard imaging practices, the association was placed on hold to prevent unvalidated traffic from entering PACS until the correct configuration could be confirmed.

At that time, I had not received notification that the modality had been fully configured, tested, and was ready for clinical use, nor was the expected AE Title provided for validation. All configurations on my end are based on the Modality Interface request and approved change details. In this case, the AE Title observed did not match what was documented in the change request, so the connection was held until the discrepancy could be resolved.

Coordination for modality setup and vendor activity is managed through BIO-MED and the department. From the imaging/infrastructure side, I rely on receiving accurate configuration details and notification when systems are ready for validation. That notification did not occur prior to the system attempting to send images.

To help prevent future occurrences, I recommend:

* Notification to imaging/infrastructure prior to go-live or testing of new modalities
* Confirmation of AE Title and routing details before clinical use
* Coordinated communication when vendors are onsite making configuration changes

Please let me know once BIO-MED or GE confirms the finalized configuration so we can move forward.

Moving forward with this, BioMed should be triple checking to make sure all thing on the medical device is setup per your request. You cannot deviate from what you are requesting. On our end that request that you submit is what we go by to create our change order. If that doesn’t match, it doesn’t get push through. Hence the hold. This should not have occurred if everything was followed through. We do not let anything come through without us knowing what it is.
